<p>Texts of his works:</p>
<ul>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.zeno.org/Soziologie/M/Weber,%20Max">Large collection of the German original texts</a></li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.uni-potsdam.de/u/paed/Flitner/Flitner/Weber/index.htm">Large collection of the German original texts</a></li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.ne.jp/asahi/moriyuki/abukuma/weber_texts.html">Large collection of English translations</a></li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.cpm.ehime-u.ac.jp/AkamacHomePage/Akamac_E-text_Links/Weber.html">Another collection of English translations</a></li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.sociosite.net/topics/weber.php">A comprehensive collection of English translations and secondary literature</a></li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://ssr1.uchicago.edu/PRELIMS/Theory/weber.html">Notes on several of Weber's works, merged into one text file</a></li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.marxists.org/reference/archive/weber/index.htm">Max Weber Reference Archive</a></li>
</ul>
<p>Analysis of his works:</p>
<ul>
